sentences: María Escribano (24 January 1954 – 22 December 2002) was a Spanish composer and music teacher.
In 1978 she received a scholarship to create the Foundation Juan March,
In 1978 she received a scholarship to create the Foundation Juan March,
and became composer-in-residence for three years at the Roy Hart Theatre Company in France, where she also worked as pianist and actress.
She also operated a music program for children aged 18 months to three years.
